    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="241"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 803/11–12.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 241.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 472 of the 8th ultimo, inclosing a copy of a note to you from
                    Prince <pb facs="0392" n="280" xml:id="pg_280"/> Ch’ing, informing you that he
                    had arranged with this department that the Chinese minister or chargé d’affaires
                    in Japan and the Chinese consul-general in Korea should issue section 6
                    certificates to Chinese of the exempt class going from those countries to the
                    United States.</p>
                <p>In this connection I inclose herewith for your information a copy of a note<note
                        n="a" xml:id="d241fna">Supra.</note> from the Chinese minister here, giving
                    a list of Chinese officials especially authorized by his Government to issue
                    section 6 certificates to Chinese of the exempt class coming to the United
                    States from other countries than China.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
